title: North Platte golf qualifies for state as team
text:
Previous Next North Platte golf qualifies for state as team 
The North Platte girls golf team qualified for state on Monday at Pacific Springs Golf Course in Omaha. Pictured from left, head coach Jim Orcutt, Riley Smith, Marissa Pascoe, Hope Wilke, Morgan Lashley, Taylor Kramer, Haley Buford and assistant coach Jeremy Stevens. Posted: Monday, October 5, 2015 3:51 pm | Updated: 5:16 pm, Mon Oct 5, 2015. North Platte golf qualifies for state as team By Andrew Bottrell abottrell@nptelegraph.com nptelegraph.com 
The North Platte golf team qualified for the state tournament on Monday shooting 371 to finish third in the A-4 District meet at Pacific Springs Golf Course in Omaha. 
“We’re feeling pretty good,” head coach Jim Orcutt said by phone. “We played a true practice round [on Sunday], taking a few extra shots from places and putting from different locations. The greens are pretty trick here. They are tricky for everybody and we handled it well.”     Subscription required
